# .loop-access.env — extra credentials your autonomous loop can use.
#
# Copy to  $CLAUDE_DIR/.loop-access.env  (default ~/.claude/.loop-access.env),
# then  chmod 600  it. run-work.sh injects every KEY=value below onto the
# `claude -p` pass env ONLY — the loop's agent and its worker bash see them
# (so it can deploy, auth a registry, hit an API); the supervisor process and
# unrelated children never inherit them.
#
# Format: raw `KEY=value`, one per line. No quotes. `export ` optional. `#` = comment.
# This is for SECRETS only. MCP servers (browser, e2e, Chrome), skills, and ssh
# are already inherited from the same ~/.claude — nothing to wire for those.
#
# GH_TOKEN (git push) and CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN (headless auth) have their own
# dedicated files (.loop-git-env / .headless-env) — don't duplicate them here.

# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=cf_xxx
# FLY_API_TOKEN=fly_xxx
# DOCKER_REGISTRY_TOKEN=xxx
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-xxx
